results.name: Expansion of q^(1/6) * eta(q) / eta(q^5) in powers of q.
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
formula: Expansion of 1 / (G(x) * H(x)) = G(x^5)^2 - x * G(x^5) * H(x^5) - x^2 * H(x^5)^2 in powers of x where G(), H() are the Rogers-Ramanujan functions.
G.f. is a period 1 Fourier series which satisfies f(-1 / (180 t)) = 5^(1/2) g(t) where q = exp(2 Pi i t) and g() is the g.f. of A035959.
Given g.f. A(x), then B(x) = A(x^3)^2 / x satisfies 0 = f(B(x), B(x^2)) where f(u, v) = u^3 + v^3 - 5*u*v - u^2*v^2.
Given g.f. A(x), then B(x) = A(x^3)^2 / x satisfies 0 = f(B(x), B(x^2), B(x^4)) where f(u, v, w) = v * u^2 * w^2 + 5 * u * w * (u + w) - v^2 * (u^2 + u*w + w^2).
G.f.: 1 / (Product_{k>0} P(5, x^k)) where P(n,x) is the n-th cyclotomic polynomial.
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ QPochhammer[ x] / QPochhammer[ x^5], {x, 0, n}]; (* _Michael Somos_, Jun 26 2014 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = local(A); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x + A) / eta(x^5 + A), n))};
